<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-19T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25663:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé at Tangier (<persName type="to">Childs</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-20T00:00:00-04:00">November 20, 1942—midnight.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>239. Your 617, Nov. 14, noon. In as much as it is believed that
                                Murphy had this subject in mind, the Department suggests that you
                                communicate your query to him.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>